      </accessrestrict>
      <userestrict id="aspace_4a8591ce47e3b1ffd04f083ba39c8e55">
         <head>Conditions Governing Use</head>
         <p>Copyright has not been transferred to Yale University.</p>  
      </userestrict>
      <prefercite id="aspace_101ad6ac825fa22eee3712d8b661a65f">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Collection of Canadian Bookplates, Robert B. Haas Family Arts Library, Yale University.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_5f1d803ae0dd276d103f2095335176f0">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>This collection comprises mostly 19th- and early 20th-century Canadian bookplates. It includes both private bookplates as well as institutional ones. Among the artists represented are the following: William Walker Alexander, W. J. Beattie, Stanley Harrod, J. E. H. MacDonald, and Arthur Howard Noll.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_73f87a1be6a189786084bef53e18f479">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>Organized into three series: I. Bookplates – Individuals. II. Bookplates – Institutions. III. Bookplates from a scrapbook.</p>  
      </arrangement>
